---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliation & Seminar Information"
  description="Information on how to affiliate with the Seishinkai Karate-do Federation. We accept affiliation inquiries from school clubs, hobby groups, community circles, and culture schools, and also offer seminars for companies and schools."
  lang="en"
  path="/en/membership/affiliation/"
>
  <section class="dojo-list">
    <div class="page-container">
      <div class="section__title-area">
        <span class="section-label">AFFILIATION</span>
        <h1 class="section-title">How to Affiliate with the Seishinkai Karate-do Federation</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/kameikanban.jpg"
            alt="How to affiliate with the Seishinkai Karate-do Federation"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-page__lead">
        If you represent a school club, hobby group, community circle, culture school, or other organization that wishes to join Seishinkai, or if you are planning to open a new class, please contact us.<br />
        In addition to our regular class activities, we also offer seminars for companies, schools, and circles upon request.
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">▼ Clubs & Circles Wishing to Affiliate</h2>
      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/Image3.jpg"
            alt="Activities of an affiliated club or circle"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
      <p>
        Circles, school clubs, and hobby groups that don't belong to any particular style often find that no formal rank certificates can be issued, and practice tends to become self-taught.<br />
        There are also cases where a group once had an instructor affiliated with a style, but lost that connection due to a transfer or other circumstances and became more of an informal hobby group — some of these groups are now operating as official branches of Seishinkai.<br />
        Seishinkai as an organization is not primarily competition-focused, but we place no restriction on members entering other tournaments, including sun-dome (non-contact) or full-contact events.<br />
        Many of our members hold ranks earned in other styles※ before transferring to Seishinkai.<br />
        Please feel free to contact us for a consultation.
      </p>
      <p class="detail-page__note">
        ※Wado-ryu, Shotokan-related styles, Goju-ryu, Shito-ryu, Shorinji-ryu, Kyokushin-related styles, Seidokaikan, Ashihara Kaikan, Shorinji Kempo, and others
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">▼ Culture Schools & Community Classes</h2>
      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/Image4.jpg"
            alt="Instruction at a culture school or community class"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
      <p>
        If your culture school is considering opening a new class or adding an additional one, please contact us for a consultation.<br />
        Seishinkai Karate is currently taught at several culture schools, and our classes rank among the top in terms of enrollment.<br />
        Courteous, attentive instruction combined with enjoyable practice is one of the key factors behind this growth in student numbers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">◆ About Our Seminars</h2>
      <p>
        If you can gather 5 or more participants, we can arrange a "Health Karate Seminar," a "Women's Self-Defense Seminar," or a seminar for companies, schools, and other organizations.<br />
        These seminars can also be used as new-employee training to strengthen mental resilience. We also offer trial/experience seminars for international tourists.<br />
        For more details, please contact the Seishinkai office by email.
      </p>

      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/top3.jpg"
            alt="Scenes from seminars and events"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/Image5.jpg"
            alt="Presentation of a rank certificate"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>▲Presentation of a rank certificate</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/bb1.jpg"
            alt="Branch head appointment certificate"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>▲Branch head appointment certificate</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/Image7.jpg"
            alt="Instructional visit to the Shizuoka branch"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>▲Instructional visit to the Shizuoka branch</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/Image8.jpg"
            alt="Seminar for company employees"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>Seminar for company employees</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-page__back">
        <a href="/en/membership/">← Back to Membership Information</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
